<div id="review_5967534" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/5967534" />
    <a title="Alto2" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/355087-alto2"><img alt="Alto2" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1189390883p2/355087.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/5967534?book_show_action=true">Sep 09, 2007</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Alto2" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Alto2" href="/user/show/355087-alto2">Alto2</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer5967534" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17891173737494772493">This debut-novel from Iranian-born Dalia Sofer has received great critical acclaim. I was hoping to like it as much as <i> The Kite Runner</i> or <i>Reading Lolita In Tehran</i>, but I didn&apos;t. The story-line and plot were compelling, but the author hardly explored the depths of her interesting characters. They felt more like caricatures. <br/><br/>Sofer has great promise as a writer. This novel reminds me a lot of Julia Glass&apos;s <i>Three Junes</i>: good, not great, and followed by an outstanding second novel. I look forward to</span>
  <span id="freeText17891173737494772493" style="display:none">This debut-novel from Iranian-born Dalia Sofer has received great critical acclaim. I was hoping to like it as much as <i> The Kite Runner</i> or <i>Reading Lolita In Tehran</i>, but I didn't. The story-line and plot were compelling, but the author hardly explored the depths of her interesting characters. They felt more like caricatures. <br /><br />Sofer has great promise as a writer. This novel reminds me a lot of Julia Glass's <i>Three Junes</i>: good, not great, and followed by an outstanding second novel. I look forward to Ms. Sofer's next book.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17891173737494772493" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


